# LedFX AirPlay Configuration
#
# This file documents configuration options for the LedFX AirPlay stack.
# Most configuration is done through the config files directly rather than
# environment variables.
#
# Note: Currently, this stack does not use a .env file. This is here for
# documentation purposes and potential future configuration options.

# Installation Directory (used by install.sh)
# Override the default installation path
# Default: /opt/ledfx-airplay
# INSTALL_DIR=/opt/ledfx-airplay

# Configuration Files
# - AirPlay device name: Edit configs/shairport-sync.conf (general.name)
# - LedFX settings: Configure via web UI at http://localhost:8888
# - Audio device: Set to "pulse" in LedFX web UI (Settings → Audio)

# Ports Used
# - 8888: LedFX web UI (HTTP)
# - 7000: Shairport-Sync AirPlay (TCP)
# - 5353: mDNS/Avahi discovery (UDP)

# Docker Images
# The stack uses :latest tags by default. To pin specific versions, edit
# docker-compose.yml and change:
#   image: ghcr.io/ledfx/ledfx:latest → ghcr.io/ledfx/ledfx:v2.0.95
#   image: mikebrady/shairport-sync:latest → mikebrady/shairport-sync:4.3.2

